author: @aseelmurga113
text:
Haegeum - Unlocking something that's forbidden.

This is my interpretation: This Agust D Music Video may represent Yoongi freeing himself from his own negative feelings and traumas, but it may also represent him liberating himself from the fixed stereotypes and perceptions of the K-Pop Idol.

He questions why idols are held to such a high standard, put under a microscope, and criticized heavily when they go against the industry norms. He purposely does something, like smoking (that would typically cause controversy) just to show people that he shouldn't have to live his life walking on eggshells, nor should anyone else. 

As an artist, he wants to create music for a long time, but he wants to be able to do it his way and freely express his thoughts without having to worry about other people's judgments.

BTS's legacy will be them breaking the genre's mold and influencing change.
